# Yulin Zhang, 2026.3.2

This folder contains scripts used to run simulations from Section S5 and S8. With the script and steps below, one should be able to reproduce simulations and TRACE analysis on the simulation outcomes.

## Step 1: Run simulations, hmmix, ibdmix and prepare singer job files

For this step 1, one needs to run the snakemake workflow. Please edit the config.yaml file with correct paths. To test the workflow, one could run 

```
snakemake --dry-run
```

If the config file are correctly modified, this should run with no error.

## Step 2: Submit sbatch jobs to run SINGER

After the first step, sbatch files for SINGER runs should be ready for direct submission. One could do

```
cd results/${model}_model/singer/sbatch_files
for $i in `ls *sbatch`
do
    sbatch $i
done
```

This would submit all created jobs to run SINGER in parallel. After all SINGER jobs get finished, one could use the `merge_ARGs.py` script to convert SINGER outputs to tskit format.

```
# This would produce 300 posterior tree sequences sampled from SINGER for simulation seed s
for i in {0..299}
do
    python merge_ARGs.py --file_table results/${model}_model/singer/sbatch_files/n100_seed${s}_posterior_1.txt --output results/${model}_model/singer/n100_seed${s}_${i}.tsz
done
```

## Step 3: Run TRACE

Once SINGER has finished running and outputs are converted to `.tsz` files, one could run TRACE on the singer outputs.

```
# create a folder for TRACE
mkdir results/${model}_model/trace

# Extracting TRACE inputs from singer trees. We recommand parallelize the for loop.
indivs=$(printf "%d," {0..99} | sed 's/,$//')
for i in {250..299}
do
    trace-extract --tree-file results/${model}_model/singer/n100_seed${s}_${i}.tsz --t-archaic 15000 --individuals ${indivs} --window-size 1000 -o results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_data_t15000_${i}_ind0_99
done

# create input data files for TRACE per simulation seed
for s in {1..10} # modify based on seeds here
do
    for i in {250..299}
    do
        cat results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_data_t15000_${i}_ind0_99 >> results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_singer_inputs.txt
    done
done

# Run TRACE infer
for ind in {0..99}
do
    for s in {1..10} # modify based on seeds here
    do
        trace-infer -i ${ind} --data-files results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_singer_inputs.txt --chroms $s -o results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_infer_t15000_ind${ind}
    done
done

# Run TRACE summarize
for ind in {0..99}
do
    for s in {1..10} # modify based on seeds here
    do
        trace-summarize -f results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_infer_t15000_ind${ind} -c ${s} -o results/${model}_model/trace/n100_seed${s}_t15000_ind${ind}
    done
done
```



